From: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
Date: Sun, 6 Mar 2022 22:57:49 +0100
Subject: bluetooth: Use netif_rx().
Patch-mainline: v5.18-rc1
Git-commit: d33d0dc9275d29be68ae1bacf430e30dc112d769
References: jsc#PED-1407

Since commit
   baebdf48c3600 ("net: dev: Makes sure netif_rx() can be invoked in any context.")

the function netif_rx() can be used in preemptible/thread context as
well as in interrupt context.

Use netif_rx().

Cc: Marcel Holtmann <marcel@holtmann.org>
Cc: Johan Hedberg <johan.hedberg@gmail.com>
Cc: Luiz Augusto von Dentz <luiz.dentz@gmail.com>
Cc: linux-bluetooth@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Sebastian Andrzej Siewior <bigeasy@linutronix.de>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Lee, Chun-Yi <jlee@suse.com>
---
 net/bluetooth/6lowpan.c   |    2 +-
 net/bluetooth/bnep/core.c |    2 +-
 2 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/net/bluetooth/6lowpan.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/6lowpan.c
@@ -240,7 +240,7 @@ static int give_skb_to_upper(struct sk_b
 	if (!skb_cp)
 		return NET_RX_DROP;
 
-	return netif_rx_ni(skb_cp);
+	return netif_rx(skb_cp);
 }
 
 static int iphc_decompress(struct sk_buff *skb, struct net_device *netdev,
--- a/net/bluetooth/bnep/core.c
+++ b/net/bluetooth/bnep/core.c
@@ -400,7 +400,7 @@ static int bnep_rx_frame(struct bnep_ses
 	dev->stats.rx_packets++;
 	nskb->ip_summed = CHECKSUM_NONE;
 	nskb->protocol  = eth_type_trans(nskb, dev);
-	netif_rx_ni(nskb);
+	netif_rx(nskb);
 	return 0;
 
